# Repo Knowledge Loader Skill Equivalent

- Use this workflow when a repository should learn from another GitHub repository.
- Prefer explicit source assets such as skills, rules, memories, runbooks, and technical docs.
- If those assets are missing, infer a concise bundle from the codebase, scripts, and repository conventions.
- Store local knowledge bundles under `.ai/repo-imports/<repo-slug>/`.
- Use `.github/skills/repo-knowledge-loader/templates/external-bridge-skill.md` as the reference bridge for external repositories.
- Keep coverage aligned with Copilot and Claude Code and record support in `SUPPORTED.md`.
